The paper deals with 3D face recognition, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR). The proposed method involves the extraction of features from range images, which is a common technique in multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed method through experiments, which is a common practice in information retrieval (cs.IR).
